<ADDRESS>
Mike Epstein
&lt;<A HREF="mailto:epstein@nyiq.net">epstein@nyiq.net</A>&gt;
</ADDRESS>
<I>Thu, 20 Jun 96 11:45:07 -0400</I><PRE>

This was posted on SPAM-L, a list devoted to ending spam, by an AOL
Assistant Postmaster. He gave his permission for me to send it to you.

Date:    Wed, 19 Jun 1996 23:12:09 -0400
&gt;From:    Ray Everett-Church &lt;<A HREF="mailto:IFRITRay@AOL.COM">IFRITRay@AOL.COM</A>&gt;
Subject: Re: Interesting AOL message

&gt;From: <A HREF="mailto:bzs@world.std.com">bzs@world.std.com</A> (Barry Shein)
&gt;So I just get a "spam" complaint from an AOL postmaster threatening:
&gt;&gt;From: <A HREF="mailto:Postmaster@aol.com">Postmaster@aol.com</A>
&gt;&gt;To: <A HREF="mailto:netadmin@world.std.com">netadmin@world.std.com</A>, <A HREF="mailto:postmaster@world.std.com">postmaster@world.std.com</A>
